text: Hey guys, it’s Ro!

So many things happened in 2016 and I wanted
to make a recap video of some of my favorite
memories!

I started off the year by traveling to Seattle
and Oregon for the last 2 stops on my cookbook

tour, we did 2 awesome meet-ups I met so many
people, it was really fun!

Had a 2 page spread for Cheeseburger cupcakes
in M Magazine.
Whipped up Pokeball Parfaits with Shane Dawson.
Shane: POKEMON!

Then ate a ton of yummy popcorn for the popcorn
challenge with Shane.
Played the Pop-Tart Challenge with Alx James.

Alx: If I have ever tasted one, that is a
hot fudge sundae, box it up!

Then we deep conditioned my hair by playing
the eat it or wear it challenge.

All my dreams came true while playing the
Starbucks Challenge with my friend Justine.

Attended LA Cookie Con where I was on the
main stage panel and I got to do a big meet
and greet with you guys.

Hung out with my friends at Hallmark’s Home
and Family and made some Hidden Heart Cupcakes.

Received a Taste Award for Breakout Foodie
of the Year.

Attended my friend Lilly’s premiere of A
Trip to Unicorn Island.

Her movie was amazing and I went with all
of the girlfriends, we dressed up as Unicorns
to be super supportive, and we had a blast!

Created masterpieces playing the blindfolded
drawing challenge game with my friend Max.

Decorated the world’s most beautiful cakes
during the cake decorating challenge on Justine’s
channel.

Played the No Thumbs challenge game and the
cereal challenge with Captain Sparklez.

Baked up some Bilbo Seed Cake Muffins with
Dominic Monaghan.
Dominic: This would get you up to Mordor.

Guessed words for the Urban Dictionary Challenge
and made a Five Nights at Freddies Giant Cupcake
with Markiplier.
Markiplier: This is adorable.
Made some Adventure Time Pancakes with Dawin.
Both: Bacon Pancakes!

Tried a lot of Custom Macarons for the Macaron
Challenge and got soaked playing the Battleship
Challenge with Captain Sparklez.

Spent some quality time with my girls, had
them over for the season premiere of Game
of Thrones, da-da-dun-dun-dun, da-da-dun-dun-dun.
Call me Kit!

Partnered with Dragonvale to make a really
cool custom cake that they actually put into
the video game.

Won a people’s choice Webby Award for an
episode of Nerdy Nummies.

Attended the White House Correspondents Dinner
and met a bunch of awesome people.

Visited the Stock Exchange floor for the first
time to talk with John and Carl on CNBC’s

Show Squawk Alley to talk about all things
YouTube.

Made Marshmallow Fondant with Carla Hall on
The Chew.

Attended YouTube’s Brandcast and had a fun
sweets booth set up for everyone.

Attended the Red Carpet Premiere of The Angry
Birds Movie.

Made some magical Unicorn Emoji Cookies with my
friend Lilly Singh.
Frosting Unicorn!
Attended Blizzard’s Warcraft Movie Premiere.

Was cast in YouTube Red’s Series Bad Internet
as Chef Sarah.

Tried many weird popsicle flavors and was
a guest on Ingrid’s show Sense of Self.

Baked up some Hedgehog Cream Puffs with The
Warp Zone.

Attended VidCon and was on the #GirlLove Panel
with my favorite gals, and, had an awesome
meet-up with you guys.

Traveled to France for the very first time
where I got to cook and stay in Julia Child’s
former kitchen.

Was on Home and Family again for their Christmas
in July to Make Candy Cane Chocolate Bark
Lollipops.

Ate way too much candy during the Giant Candy
Challenge with my friend Jake.

Baked Spider Donuts from the game Undertale
with Dan and Phil.
Phil: Oh, ow!

Manny and I got a makeover playing the not
my arms makeup challenge.

Met 2 amazing young ladies through the Make-A-Wish
Foundation, we made Minecraft Cookies with
Erica and her sisters.

And, played the Goldfish Challenge and heads
up with Eva.

Tasted delicious cheesecake during the Cheesecake
Challenge with fellow foodie Donal Skeehan.

Then on his channel, we tried some new recipes
on Dirty Little Food Secrets.

Gargled some songs and played the Whisper
Challenge with Madelyn Bailey.

Voiced the character Miss Blissful in The
Fine Brothers animated show Emo Dad.

Imitated animals playing the Heads Up Challenge
with Lindsay Stirling.
Ro: Ribbit, ribbit.
Lindsay: A, oh Toad!

Made Cookie Cat Ice Cream Sandwiches with
Jake.
Ro: Jake, don’t do it!
Jake: I, I can…
Ro: Jake share!

Visited my friends at Home and Family for the third
time to make a quick and easy back to school recipe.

Starred in a Best Fiends commercial with Joey
Graceffa and Kate Walsh.

Ate a lot of pizza for the Cheese Pizza Challenge,
with Justine.

I’m so disappointed in myself I can’t
even talk about it right now!

My dog Cookie turned 2 years old and I made
her some Dog treats to celebrate!
Went on Grace Helbig’s Podcast Not Too Deep.

Sang some Opera on Shane Dawson’s Podcast
Shane and Friends.
Did the Starbucks Challenge Part 2, with Justine.
I gotta taste some more!
Oh no I ate my ring!
Reached 7 Million Subscribers on YouTube!

Made Geode Candy Cupcakes from my cookbook
with Joey.

Was featured in a 2 page spread for People
Magazine’s Special Holiday Recipes.

Got pretty messy and drenched again playing
the Pie Face Game, and Wet Head challenge
with Markiplier.
Was on several episodes of YouTubers React.
Attended the premiere of Haters Back Off.

Had a recipe featured in People Magazine’s
Halloween Edition.

The German version of the Nerdy Nummies Cookbook
was published.
Danke, danke, danke, danke!
That means thank you!

Baked with the one and only Cookie Monster
on Nerdy Nummies.
Cookie: Oh me going down!
Ro: Oh no!
Cookie: What a clean floor you have here!

The Nerdy Nummies Cookbook celebrated it’s
first birthday.

Baked Tribble Themed Macaroons with the cast
of Star Trek: Next Generation on Home and
Family.
Played the Cookie Challenge with Jake.
Jake: We did it!
Ro: It’s it, it’s it!
Jake: Awwww!
Ro: Ding-ding!
Apple Pie!

Sang a Harry Potter Acapella with The Warp
Zone.

Then for the Holidays I decorated some Themed
Gingerbread Houses with Justine.
Justine: Don’t make fun of it!

And we also made an Apple Store Gingerbread
House on her channel.

Guest starred on Disney’s TV Show, Bizaardvark
for their holiday episode.
Baked Holiday Pizzas with my dad Papa Pizza!

Was a part of YouTube Rewind with so many
other amazing people, I got to have a big

pillow fight and cuddle with some of my favorite
YouTubers.

Geeked out attending the Star Wars: Rogue
One World Premiere.

Started the process of moving into my new
home.
One!

Filmed the first Nerdy Nummies in the new
kitchen.
Oh pfft!

Built a Minecraft Shron Snow Golem Cake with
Captain Sparklez.

Attempted to guess crazy candy cane flavors
with Sam Tsui.
You should be brown?

Very carefully crafted some YouTube Play Button
Cupcakes with Markiplier.
Ahhhh!

Also played the play dough challenge with
Markiplier on his channel.

Celebrated the new year with my girls going
beast mode!
As Belle on Cassey’s channel.

And throughout the year we made a ton of Nerdy
Nummies.

Alright, I hope you guys enjoyed the recap
video and you had a wonderful 2016, let’s
make 2017 just as fun.
Bye-bye!
